definitions.definition: A porridge made by boiling hulled wheat , typically with additional ingredients such as milk, egg yolks , and/or almond milk, traditionally served with venison or porpoise .
examples: Frumenty was often the first dish on the menu of a medieval English feast.

main_definition: ( chiefly historical ) A porridge made by boiling hulled wheat , typically with additional ingredients such as milk, egg yolks , and/or almond milk, traditionally served with venison or porpoise .
